Execute only PHASE 10.3.

Goal:
Implement billing provider adapter interface, mock billing adapter, Stripe-compatible shell, subscription service, invoice service, webhooks, and Billing API.

Create/update:
backend/app/billing/billing_adapters.py
backend/app/billing/mock_billing_adapter.py
backend/app/billing/stripe_adapter.py
backend/app/billing/subscription_service.py
backend/app/billing/invoice_service.py
backend/app/billing/billing_webhooks.py
backend/app/api/billing.py

Update:
backend/app/main.py
backend/app/audit/audit_service.py
backend/app/core/events.py
backend/app/auth/rbac.py
backend/app/auth/dependencies.py

Tests:
backend/app/tests/test_subscription_service.py
backend/app/tests/test_mock_billing_adapter.py
backend/app/tests/test_billing_api.py

BillingProviderAdapter methods:
- create_customer(organization)
- create_checkout_session(organization_id, plan_id)
- get_subscription(provider_subscription_id)
- cancel_subscription(provider_subscription_id)
- create_billing_portal_session(organization_id)
- handle_webhook(payload, signature)

Mock billing adapter:
- deterministic fake customer IDs
- deterministic fake subscription IDs
- fake checkout URL
- fake billing portal URL
- no external API calls
- works in tests

Stripe adapter shell:
- Stripe-compatible structure
- no crash if stripe SDK missing
- real mode requires STRIPE_ENABLED=true and keys
- never logs Stripe secret key
- webhook signature verification placeholder fails safely if secret missing
- do not store raw card data

Subscription service methods:
- get_status(organization_id) -> dict
- list_plans() -> list[BillingPlan]
- start_checkout(organization_id, plan_id) -> dict
- open_billing_portal(organization_id) -> dict
- cancel_subscription(organization_id) -> Subscription
- sync_subscription_from_provider(organization_id) -> Subscription
- apply_mock_plan(organization_id, plan_tier) -> Subscription

Rules:
- apply_mock_plan allowed only in development or admin mode.
- Plan change audited.
- Subscription status affects entitlements.
- Suspended subscription blocks paid features.
- Free tier remains available unless organization is suspended.

Billing API:
GET  /api/billing/status
GET  /api/billing/plans
GET  /api/billing/subscription
POST /api/billing/checkout
POST /api/billing/portal
POST /api/billing/cancel
POST /api/billing/mock/apply-plan
GET  /api/billing/usage
GET  /api/billing/usage/{metric}
GET  /api/billing/invoices
POST /api/billing/webhooks/provider

Rules:
- Auth required except provider webhook.
- Tenant scoped.
- Admin/owner can manage subscription.
- Viewer can read billing status only if allowed.
- Webhook must not require user auth but must verify provider signature when real provider enabled.
- All billing actions audited.
- Use standard API response shape.
- Error codes:
  BILLING_PROVIDER_NOT_CONFIGURED
  SUBSCRIPTION_INACTIVE
  PLAN_NOT_FOUND
  FEATURE_NOT_ENTITLED
  QUOTA_EXCEEDED

Events:
billing.plan.listed
billing.checkout.started
billing.subscription.updated
billing.subscription.canceled
billing.invoice.synced
billing.webhook.received
billing.webhook.failed

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

